  "headline": "Renaissance Science",
  "description": "Renaissance science (15th-17th centuries) broke from Aristotelian/medieval frameworks. Key figures: Leonardo da Vinci (anatomy, engineering), Copernicus (heliocentric cosmology), Vesalius (modern anatomy, De Humani Corporis Fabrica, 1543), Galileo (experimental physics, telescopic astronomy). The printing press spread knowledge faster than ever before.",
